<paragraph id="252D36E5FFB5587FFF30FF79E7FCF739" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
Shrub, 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFF4CFF79E219F4C8" box="[235,279,152,178]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
high. Branches terete, covered with short yellow erect trichomes; nodes with 2 glands lateral to the base of the petiole, umbonate, each gland 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFD35FF5FE02CF4A2" box="[658,802,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.1 mm</quantity>
diam.; internodes 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFBA5FF5FE78CF4A2" box="[1026,1154,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12–16 mm</quantity>
long. Leaves alternate; petiole 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFF48FF04E271F485" box="[239,383,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.5 mm</quantity>
, pilose, trichomes short, adpress; blade coriaceous, ovate to elliptic, 3.8–5.6 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFA81FF04E696F485" box="[1318,1432,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="cm" value="2.3" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.0">2–2.6 cm</quantity>
, apex acute, base rounded, margin straight, glabrous to glabrescent, trichomes, when present, restricted to the base and close to the petiole, adaxial surface glossy, pilose only at the base of the primary vein, abaxial surface opaque, glabrescent, more densely along the primary vein; venation broquidodromous, primary vein slightly raised above and well visible below, secondary veins slightly raised on both surfaces. Raceme axillary or terminal, lax, 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFEC5FE47E2F6F5BA" box="[354,504,422,448]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.15" metricValueMax="10.1" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="cm" value="8.15" valueMax="10.1" valueMin="6.2">6.2–10.1 cm</quantity>
long; rachis angled to flat, pubescent, trichomes yellowish, short, dense and adpressed; pedicel 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFEDBFE2CE2F6F59D" box="[380,504,461,487]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.0">3–3.7 mm</quantity>
, sericeous, with umbonate to short terete glands attached to the base, 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFAE5FE2CE3C7F674" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.7 mm</quantity>
. Bracts and bracteoles persistent, sericeous, bracts foliaceous, 2.6–6.2 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFB95FE15E7CAF674" box="[1074,1220,500,526]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="2.9" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.9 mm</quantity>
, bracteoles linear, 1.2–1.6 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFEB5FDFBE2A9F64E" box="[274,423,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
. Flowers yellow, 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFDDBFDFBE015F64E" box="[636,795,538,564]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.45" metricValueMax="10.3" metricValueMin="8.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="9.45" valueMax="10.3" valueMin="8.6">8.6–10.3 mm</quantity>
long. External sepals free from each other, adaxially pilose, ciliate, the upper sepals ovate, 3.8 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFD05FDA0E1F1F621" box="[674,767,577,603]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
, the lower sepal cimbiform, 5 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFB22FDA0E7EBF621" box="[1157,1253,577,603]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
. Internal sepals obovate with a short claw, adaxially pilose, ciliate, 9.5 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFCEEFD89E0A9F6F8" box="[841,935,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
, inflexed at the apex. Corolla with lateral petals spatulate, shortly unguiculate, ciliate, 7.8–8 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFCB3FD6FE0A8F6D2" box="[788,934,654,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.6">3.6–3.7 mm</quantity>
, apex truncate. Rudimentary petals scalelike, about 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFEBAFD54E276F6B5" box="[285,376,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long. Carina about 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFDC2FD54E1CEF6B5" box="[613,704,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="8.6">8.6 mm</quantity>
long, ciliate, cristate (unguicule: 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFBF5FD54E798F6B5" box="[1106,1174,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, cucule: 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFAE6FD54E695F6B5" box="[1345,1435,693,719]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long, crest: 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFE87FD3DE276F68C" box="[288,376,732,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long). Stamens with a filament sheath about 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFC20FD3DE0C5F68C" box="[903,971,732,758]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
long, fleshy, pilose at the base, margins and dorsal portion. Ovary 1 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFE5AFCE3E154F766" box="[509,602,770,796]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, gibbose, sessile, densely pubescent at the gibbous region and near the base, sessile; style 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFED3FCC8E2C0F739" box="[372,462,809,835]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="6.9">6.9 mm</quantity>
long, uncinate, glabrous, stigma bilobed. Fruits and seeds unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6D88656EFFB5587FFF61FCB1E233F7EA" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="252D36E5FFB5587FFF61FCB1E233F7EA" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFF61FCB1E27AF710" bold="true" box="[198,372,848,874]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The epithet of this new species refers to Marajó Island, where the only known specimen was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6D88656EFFB5587FFF61FC7CE736F169" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="252D36E5FFB5587FFF61FC7CE066F7A4" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFF61FC7CE10CF7CD" bold="true" box="[198,514,925,951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="E2924D66FFB5587FFD87FC7DE027F7CC" authorityName="C.S.Costa, A.C.A.Aguiar-Dias &amp; A.O.Simoes" authorityYear="2013" box="[544,809,924,950]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Securidaca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marajoara">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFD87FC7DE027F7CC" box="[544,809,924,950]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Securidaca marajoara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only for the 
<typeStatus id="FA298847FFB5587FFB9EFC7CE765F7CD" box="[1081,1131,925,951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
collection, from northern 
<collectingCountry id="5D857675FFB5587FFF30FC25E3ECF7A4" box="[151,226,964,990]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. It grows in the Amazon Rainforest, in riverine forests.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="252D36E5FFB5587FFF61FC0BE202F051" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFF61FC0BE25CF07E" bold="true" box="[198,338,1002,1028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Phenology:</emphasis>
—The species was collected during its flowering period in January. The fruiting period is unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="252D36E5FFB5587FFF61FBD9E736F169" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFF61FBD9E23DF028" bold="true" box="[198,307,1080,1106]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E2924D66FFB5587FFE94FBD6E133F02B" authorityName="C.S.Costa, A.C.A.Aguiar-Dias &amp; A.O.Simoes" authorityYear="2013" box="[307,573,1079,1105]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Securidaca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marajoara">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFE94FBD6E133F02B" box="[307,573,1079,1105]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Securidaca marajoara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its large and conspicuous bracts, persistent at flower anthesis, by its relatively long inflorescences (
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFD11FBBFE047F002" box="[694,841,1118,1144]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.15" metricValueMax="10.1" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="cm" value="8.15" valueMax="10.1" valueMin="6.2">6.2–10.1 cm</quantity>
long), small, ovate to elliptic leaves (3.8–5.6 × 
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFAD9FBBFE3E4F0E5" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="cm" value="2.3" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.0">2– 2.6 cm</quantity>
) and short internodes (
<quantity id="E26A9B00FFB5587FFDA7FB64E18CF0E5" box="[512,642,1157,1183]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12–16 mm</quantity>
long). The species is sympatric and morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E2924D66FFB5587FFA22FB65E2FAF0BC" authority="Bentham (1851: 162)" authorityName="Bentham" authorityPageNumber="162" authorityYear="1851" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Securidaca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bialata">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFA22FB65E3E5F0BF" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">S. bialata</emphasis>
Bentham (1851: 162)
</taxonomicName>
, with similarities regarding the shape of the petiolar and pedicelar glands, leaf size, inflorescence size and architecture, and flower size. Despite their resemblance, the two species can be easily distinguished by the larger, persistent and elliptic bracts of 
<taxonomicName id="E2924D66FFB5587FFC31FB19E73FF168" authorityName="C.S.Costa, A.C.A.Aguiar-Dias &amp; A.O.Simoes" authorityYear="2013" box="[918,1073,1272,1298]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygalaceae" genus="Securidaca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marajoara">
<emphasis id="17E6EAF7FFB5587FFC31FB19E73FF168" box="[918,1073,1272,1298]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">S. marajoara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
